name: Class EventTypeInfo
codes:
public final class EventTypeInfo
extends Object

methods.description:
Returns the label, a human-readable name, associated with the event type
 for this EventTypeInfo (for example, "Garbage Collection").

Returns the list of human-readable names that makes up the category for this
 EventTypeInfo (for example, "Java Virtual Machine" or "Garbage Collector").

Returns the unique ID for the event type associated with this
 EventTypeInfo, not guaranteed to be the same for different Java
 Virtual Machines (JVMs) instances.

Returns the name for the event type associated with this
 EventTypeInfo (for example, "jdk.GarbageCollection").

Returns a short sentence or two describing the event type associated with
 this EventTypeInfo, for example
 "Garbage collection performed by the JVM"".

Returns settings for the event type associated with this
 EventTypeInfo.
Returns a description of this EventTypeInfo.

Returns an EventType represented by the specified
 CompositeData

 The supplied CompositeData must have the following item names and
 item types to be valid. 

The name and type the specified CompositeData must contain


Name
Type




id
Long


name
String


label
String


description
String


category
ArrayType(1, SimpleType.STRING)


settings
javax.management.openmbean.CompositeData[] whose element type
 is the mapped type for SettingDescriptorInfo as specified in the
 SettingDescriptorInfo.from(javax.management.openmbean.CompositeData) method.
